result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Raychel M Eckel

records.addlTxt: No controlled substances without a valid prescription. $2500
No controlled substances without a valid prescription.

8:15 AM Defendant Raychel M Eckel appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Gavin Grubofski in court for Raychel M Eckel.  Attorney Jennifer Zima in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Jacob Paltz is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Zima. He is a police officer with the Wisconsin Rapids Police Department. On 10/14/22, he performed a traffic stop for an expired registration. The driver of the vehicle was identified as the defendant. The witness identifies defendant in the courtroom. He had his canine perform a free air sniff of the vehicle and it indicated on the vehicle. He searched the vehicle and he located a bag with a white crystal substance in defendant's purse. It tested positive for methamphetamine. Attorney Grubofski cross-examines witness.  Attorney Zima asks Court take judicial notice of Portage County case 22CF215, a case defendant was out on bond for. Court takes judicial notice.
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Not guilty plea. Attorney Grubofski is requesting that bond me modified to signature bond. State does not object. Court modifies bond to $2500 signature bond with condition of no controlled substances without a valid prescription.
Final pre-trial scheduled for January 20, 2023 at 09:00 am.
Demand for Discovery and Inspection - Defendant
